history.content: You can waitlist 170 as an undeclared. When adjustment period starts all reserved seats will expired so if there's an open seat and you're at the top of the WL, you're in. Keep in mind that if you're not declared by the end of phase II, they might re-order the waiting list on the last day to move declared CS/EECS up the waitling list.

children.subject: If it helps, I declared last December and had phase-1nd cs170 for this spring. I ended up getting in around 2 weeks after the declaration was processed (I think I was 160ish on the waitlist initially? Declaring moved me up to 80ish if not higher iirc.)

Wait if you're declared, shouldn't you just get in without having to be waitlisted (albeit in a higher position)? I had thought of phase-2-ing cs 170, but should I actually phase-1 that class if I want to take it next sem?

(for reference, I also need to be declared over the summer)
So what are the chances of getting into 170 at the end of phase 2, given that I will hopefully be declared by then?
